                          <locus target="#41r" facs="045">Fol. 41r</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang="gez">መምህር፡ ግዳይ፡</foreign>, in Tǝgrǝñña</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                          <locus target="#45r #130r" facs="049 134">Fols. 45r, 130r</locus>
                          <desc>Overlooked text is added interlinearly</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                          <locus target="#144v #145r" facs="149">Fols. 144v, 145r</locus>
                        <desc type="AcquisitionNote">Record of purchase of the manuscript, <date calendar="ethiopian" when="1944" when-custom="1952" evidence="internal">ሚያዝሃ፡ ፭ቀን፡ [፲፱]፵፬ ዓ.ም.</date> (April 23, 1952)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus>
                           <desc>Scrawl in blue ink</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <locus target="#145v" facs="150">Fol. 145v</locus>
                           <desc>blank</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                          <desc>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                            Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size.
                            But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout).
                            This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#52r" facs="056">fol. 52r</locus>)</desc>
                          </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
